column5: Hey everyone,  Just got into ice fishing this year and was planning on going to bay of quinte for walleye. I was planning on going this sunday but heard that the walleye fishing is very slow at this time and picks up later. Any validity to this?  Also, where are they located at different periods of the hardwater season?  Thanks a lot guys!  Any other information on lake trout location would be greatly appreciated as well! Thanks again
A week or so ago it was absolutely on fire.
LOL Solo... it was always good yesterday!  Lots of BOQ posts here in the last week or so live.to.fish, check the last few pages of posts in the general discussion.
Its going to be on fire Thursday 7:35am !!!
